<refnamediv>
    <refname>glite-eds-key-unregister</refname>
    <refpurpose>
        Removes the encryption key from the Hydra KeyStore.
    </refpurpose>
</refnamediv>

<refsynopsisdiv>
    <cmdsynopsis>
	<command>glite-eds-key-unregister</command>

    <group>
		<arg choice="plain"><option>-h</option></arg>
	</group>
	<group>
		<arg choice="plain"><option>-q</option></arg>
	</group>
	<group>
	        <arg choice="plain"><option>-v</option></arg>
	</group>
	<group>
		<arg choice="plain"><option>-i <replaceable>ID</replaceable></option></arg>
	</group>
	<group>
		<arg choice="plain"><option>-s <replaceable>SERVICE</replaceable></option></arg>
	</group>
    </cmdsynopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsect1>
    <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
    <para>
        <command>glite-eds-key-unregister</command> is a command-line tool for
        removing the encryption keys from Hydra KeyStore.  If you have other
        copies of files, encrypted with the given key, lying around, you will
        not be able to decrypt them anymore!
    </para>
</refsect1>

<refsect1>
    <title>OPTIONS</title>
    <variablelist>

	<varlistentry>
	    <term>
		<group choice="plain">
		    <arg choice="plain"><option>-h</option></arg>
		</group>
	    </term>
	    <listitem><para>
	        Show help screen.
	    </para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>

	<varlistentry>
	    <term>
		<group choice="plain">
		    <arg choice="plain"><option>-q</option></arg>
		</group>
	    </term>
	    <listitem><para>
	        Quiet operation.
	    </para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>

	<varlistentry>
	    <term>
		<group choice="plain">
		    <arg choice="plain"><option>-v</option></arg>
		</group>
	    </term>
	    <listitem><para>
	        Verbose operation.
	    </para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>

	<varlistentry>
	    <term>
		<group choice="plain">
		    <arg choice="plain"><option>-i <replaceable>ID</replaceable></option></arg>
		</group>
	    </term>
	    <listitem><para>
	        ID used to store the encryption data with (logical file name or GUID).
	    </para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>

	<varlistentry>
	    <term>
		<group choice="plain">
		    <arg choice="plain"><option>-s <replaceable>SERVICE</replaceable></option></arg>
		</group>
	    </term>
	    <listitem><para>
            If <option><replaceable>SERVICE</replaceable></option> starts with
            <userinput>https://</userinput>, then it it used as the endpoint of
            a Hydra KeyStore.  
            Otherwise <option><replaceable>SERVICE</replaceable></option> is
            taken as a service name, and serives discovery is used to determine
            the service endpoint.
	    </para></listitem>
	</varlistentry>

    </variablelist>
</refsect1>

